# TubeWatch TypeScript Quality Rules

## Purpose

This rule file defines TypeScript quality standards for the TubeWatch project.

All generated code must follow strict typing practices to ensure stability and maintainability.

---

## Strict Typing

Always use strict TypeScript typing.

Avoid the use of `any` unless absolutely necessary.

Prefer explicit type definitions.

---

## Function Return Types

All exported functions must define explicit return types.

Example:

export function buildChannelFeatures(): ChannelFeatures

Avoid implicit return types for exported functions.

---

## Interface and Type Usage

Use interfaces or types to define structured data.

Example:

interface VideoMetrics {
  views: number
  likes: number
  comments: number
}

This ensures consistent data structures across modules.

---

## Block-Level Types

Each block should define its own type definitions when appropriate.

Example:

src/features/feature-engine/types.ts

This keeps type definitions close to the related logic.

---

## Avoid Any

Avoid using:

any

If a type is unknown, prefer:

unknown

Or define a more specific type.

---

## Optional Fields

Use optional fields only when necessary.

Example:

interface ChannelData {
  title: string
  subscriberCount?: number
}

Avoid excessive optional typing.

---

## Type Safety

All function inputs and outputs should be typed.

Example:

function normalizeVideoMetrics(videos: Video[]): NormalizedVideoMetrics[]

Avoid untyped parameters.

---

## Reusable Types

If a type is shared across multiple modules, place it in:

src/types/

Example:

ChannelData  
VideoData  
AnalysisResult

---

## Type Imports

Use type imports when importing types.

Example:

import type { VideoMetrics } from "@/types"

This avoids unnecessary runtime imports.

---

## Type Clarity

Types should be descriptive and easy to understand.

Avoid overly complex generic types unless required.

---

## Rule Summary

TypeScript code must:

- avoid any
- use explicit return types
- define clear interfaces
- keep types modular
- ensure predictable data structures

